lass=title>   Re: Hybrid classes and AC</span><hr size=1> To funnel this back into the orginal discussion, this is not about Paladins, Rangers, or blue butt monkeys. It's about a specific class called SHADOWKNIGHTS. <br>
Experience and stories are all fine and good, but stating you know nothing about the class , or that you play another class, or that you play the class in question to level 2 then voicing your opinion regardless, taints and essentially dissolves your argument. <br>
<br>
There's one detail I have seemed to have missed in this whole thing and that is what race the young SK is. If he is of an higher int pool, then perhaps AC is ok. If he is a less than intelligent SK then INT would be much in his favor. The class I can rule out is Iksar since we are talking about plate. <br>
<br>
SK's are not Offensive tanks and brute force is not really part of the class dynamic.  <p>
<img src="http://www.users.uswest.net/~c007a/tag.jpg"><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugroulravenblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Groul Ravenblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 500<br> <font color=#CC9900>(7/18/01 7:41:37 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.austin.rr.com/theknight/images/groul-face.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hybrid classes and AC</span><hr size=1> I'd have to disagree. We are only an offensive hybrid because of our spells, yes. However our skills still lead themself toward heavy tanking. The main thing I do these days is provide clerics a specific place to dump mana. That means I'm taking a beating so they can only heal one target. I think alot of upper level(55+) shadowknights are finding this out a little late, but its been this way for a while. If you are a shadowknight, get ALL the AC you can muster, and start tanking, then get more AC, and tank more. You'll find that it makes your groups go alot smoother. Now of course there are exceptions to this, and after all warriors ARE much better tanks, however if they can't keep agro off the casters and chain classes its up to you to ensure that you die first.<br>
<br>
As far as mana goes. I'm an ogre(one of the less intelligent races I guess). I put no points into intelligence during creation. I'm at 131 int atm in my AC gear, I RARELY ever go out of mana. Like Flayh said, only if I'm pulling nonstop(ie NO medding) and I don't have Clarity. Since lifetaps pre-lvl 56 aren't all that great(well, maybe Lifeleech at 49, and even that has so long of a recast time you aren't going to go OOM casting it), I really see no reason you are going to go OOM as a shadowknight. Unless you don't wanna take the time to med up between fights. <br>
<br>
I've only recently been able to start going OOM by chain casting Drain Soul(lvl 60 lifetap) and this since I became a Grave Lord. Maybe at lvl 60 mana max makes more of a difference, I might be able to tell you in a couple months, but thus far I don't believe int/mana gear to be of ANY concern to Shadowknights. If you are concerned about it, more than likely you never tank. If you don't tank or rather refuse to tank then yes, you aren't hurting yourself by going to int/mana gear. However I don't think you are playing your class to its fullest potential.<br>
<br>
GO AC, trust me!<br>
<br>
