Sphere of Honor <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uarathena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arathena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dark Valkyrie of Innoruuk</span><br>  Posts: 409<br> <font color=#CC9900>(7/25/01 2:04:05 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hybrid classes and AC</span><hr size=1> Like Groul, I find myself working my way towards trying to be the main tank in all situations possible. If I have three clerics dumping on me, that means that all those melees we brought along can pop offensive disciplines and we can watch that thing's HP sink like a rock. <br>
<br>
Now, staying main tank means two things: Staying alive, and keeping aggro. We all know what it takes to stay alive: HP/AC. Now, conisder that 90%, or more, of your aggro as an SK is going to be from your spells. This means that at some point, you're going to have to find your own balance between HP/AC. I'd say, if the EBBP put you over the next multiple of, say, 25 or 50 on AC, then it was a good trade off. Otherwise, I think you've just traded 65ish mana for not enough effect.<br>
<br>
Just my two cents, though.  <p><center>Arathena Dracheseele<br>
54th Reaverette of Innoruuk, <br>
